-- Greenspan says bottom of home sales decline reached
-- 
-- Wed Mar 7, 2007 12:02pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/03/07/us-usa-economy-housing-greenspan-idUSNYG00053520070307

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - A bottom has been hit in the decline of U.S. home sales, said former Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan on Wednesday. 


 Greenspan was speaking at a trading technology conference in New York. He also said that the U.S. housing sector was experiencing an "inventory recession."